{
  "stem": "21626.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Were there many children who traveled with you?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think there were about 14 others in the plane.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And you know, each one of us were orphaned.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Out of all those children in the school, and there were hundreds of them who came on the transport, there was only one father who survived.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Anyway, we went, I think, in a Lancaster bomber.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I remember flying over Cologne and seeing the devastation of the city, and then flying over Prague.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was such a bright, sunny August day.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And Prague was, of course, almost untouched by bombs, which was wonderful.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But the homecoming was so strange.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There was no one waiting for me, because no one knew when the transports were bringing in the children.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But actually, my friend, Alice, whom I mentioned earlier, who's my best friend, her oldest sister who came with the liberating army to-- to-- to Theresienstadt, when that was freed, she had been going every single day to the airport in case Alice had appeared.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And so, of course, she let my aunt know I had arrived.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And she came for me the next day.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But those of us, you know, who had no parents to go to, they had a very hard time of it.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Because the government made them stay in hostels-- the ones who were sort of my age.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I was 16-- so I think from 15 onwards-- in hostels, where people who'd come back to Prague, from the concentration camps, and had nowhere to go were living.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Now, these people, of course, were in dreadful states-- mentally, emotionally, physically-- as you can imagine.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
